Staff needs to be little mannered and they should hire some young crowd for such busy resto. We were looked by an aged uncle for which we had to repeat the order multiple times.
They should only keep dine in and not online orders because of which most of the orders get delayed. [{"Name":"Vikrant Kembhavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW8KY-n5t2Owa5elZDi3NxcdsoFXMe0zXBObWSxsKQwO18=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Quite an old family restaurant situated in the heart of Dombivli suburb. The food taste and quantity has been surpassing all expectations since the past few decades now.
The owner and his son being very old acquaintances to us, always go an extra mile to ensure that we are comfortable and are enjoying our time. Even got us a complimentary sweet dish on the house for a special occasion i.e. birthday.
Only suggestion being - if they could refurbish & renovate the place to keep up with the current times.","Images":null,"When":"3 weeks ago"},{"Name":"vimal pasad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEyq62G3Jlxi5bWkh9cG9HIkClY8uXDfdJQxImANxO1OI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always loved the food here.
The owner visits each & every table by himself so that he can improve his services & asks his guests if everything s okay with food & service","Images":null,"When":"a week ago"},{"Name":"Pallavi Salunke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdTCRv3RqfGf2aJSZn4eMeSiUDcDgzNwmIV0wJRtkXoFdC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We ordered chicken sandwich and chicken hot and sour. Sandwich was bland, I did not like the taste much. The other dish was good. Although the service were too slow. We ordered two different cocktails but they made with same juice so I had to replace my cocktail. Also the restaurant were not even loaded with the guests.","Images":null,"When":"a month ago"},{"Name":"Amol Chaskar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUewDJb_8cHDyjdr2rGqjWkoBPksvZTeyHwCJ8BwHx2Ryw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ambience is really good, it has old charm feels really good, it's simple yet attractive, staff is good and food is good as well.

The bestest dish - Chana Garlic Fry, you can have it during drinks for munching, but this kind of quality and taste hard to find.

Chinese food taste can be improved.

Overall good experience.

This review is about Rangoli Family Restaurant which is on 1st floor.","Images":null,"When":"2 months ago"},{"Name":"Gaurav Kanchan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfNJGHhEePjWXTb53G4RAvRYXvA2DUp8A0QS6qMi-4fFY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food wise everything would have been a 5/5 except the Bhaasa fish fry which was tooooo salty and when requested a change, we received a similar level of salinity in the replaced dish.

Atmosphere- Inspite of the AC, I was sweating. The cooling was not adjusted.

Had a family dinner with my parents on a Saturday, would like to appreciate the servers and waiters there, who were too polite and welcoming otherwise.","Images":null,"When":"a month ago"},{"Name":"pacemakers4u","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzHynU-VStBdTMQd3YHp2BVSoMCNgcAnpEUGYn_2ikWMo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best & oldest Family restaurant in Dombivli. Still Maintaining their standard & Taste. Owners Mr.Shetty sir is Very Humble and will guide you to have meal according to your preference. Great ambiance for Family.
And also have 2 saperate sections for Bachlores ( Gents)","Images":null,"When":"3 months ago"},{"Name":"Shruti A Shet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL7eC0jo-41cXazUnw8JN5xGJguI3XNN3XszuGMmWpF=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We had ordered chicken oil fry lollypop
However, it was tasteless and bland.
We reached out to the manager and got it replaced. However, it was not that great. After that we ordered Dal khichdi tadka. To our surprise, it was just dal rice with excess of water. Seems as if the chef has no idea how it's made.
We had to leave that as well.
Highly disappointed with the food we got.
The quality of the food has drastically gone down üëé","Images":null,"When":"3 months ago"},{"Name":"Mayur Sawant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3oQmzrWfpFHKXdz1NwFgZfJKh3pyrOlt24W-qFYncYccd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The service provided by the restaurant seems to be degraded year by year. Would barely consider visiting again.","Images":null,"When":"5 months ago"}]

[{"Name":"Tejashree Khare","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGvqVi6fmNSMEV_PCiCGejTeFkCz_FqeAwy9OGY8YymXFZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"They serve veg and nonveg food here. The food is delicious. The quantity of food is good enough as per their cost. You can visit this place with your friends and family.
Me and my family ordered starters as spring rolls, chicken crispy, chicken seekh kabab. Then in the main course we ordered butter chicken and butter rotis. All the dishes were tasty with reasonable prices.","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPZy_VbBsUjudPjDipUEFTSqLjw2zbuWKzsGIB-=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOuBHY6zkqDpxEIpqMj6n0DHIxAkU7SFo_2L2hi=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMdI0CFm2NGEelO0PO4QqEzwfngsHH13gwiMfXX=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNZb7ywT7RYIQsCqmKu_Ne3b8ZWFpx91whC2GAw=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPndayQMklbOLScqZVGtbHd8266OZnEwNefjNAo=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"6 months ago"},{"Name":"Prashant Nikam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdv4qlXMMft_roDTvRsmFgCTDKWGi9AEqPv_wN19Q_EoM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Modern's Kitchen in Dombivli East is a culinary gem with delightful offerings and exceptional service. The contemporary ambiance adds to the inviting experience. The menu impresses with a blend of classic and innovative dishes, catering to various tastes. Flavors are on point, and presentation reflects the chef's skill. Fresh ingredients elevate each dish, leaving a lasting impression. Generous portions offer excellent value for money. The restaurant maintains high cleanliness standards, ensuring a safe environment. Efficient service ensures a comfortable dining experience. Modern's Kitchen is a must-visit for food enthusiasts seeking diverse and delicious dishes in a modern setting. Highly recommended!","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNv2tqxYG9zkXV6btrDhz3nC_nrRoBuOnp-gswe=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"2 months ago"},{"Name":"Rabindranath Chanda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVw8mgW0cpgbt3SvRZNjkUyPrOoP8fE6FQStvIKzpn4RSo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is centrally situated,very near to Dombivali railway station and vegetable market.
They serve vegetarian and non veg dishes,veg dishes like masala dhosa,rice plate,etc,and non veg dishes like chicken biryani, mutton biriyani, chicken spring roll etc.
Food is tasty, good service and reasonable price.","Images":null,"When":"3 weeks ago"},{"Name":"Pranav S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKBOEKSksZ7eMpU7bgZ3Xn1ku5U8djTdfLbimZ_B9761g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Please find a better spot than the present (veg market) or the previous one (opp railway station). Cleanliness not up to Modern Cafe levels (which is the top of the town restaurant). The staff is not tidy and well dressed.
Also, tandoor items are always a bit more salty. Curry items are very tasty and perfect.

For all the above your genuine customers will definitely pay a higher price.","Images":null,"When":"a month ago"},{"Name":"shweta shetty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAhpYLRrEzDyErkwnXvYLqFyjj2mTgm6oRnUuUizopOMlM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was fantastic specially pot chicken rice garlic chicken Kung pao chicken üòãüòãüòãüòãüòãüòã and that Korean kimchi added a lot of zest","Images":null,"When":"2 months ago"},{"Name":"Sonal Rasam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJqe3MxZNIe7DGjwTaJDDtswc_bJuBljpQexauv0rZ1qg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Chinese restaurant in Dombivli East.
So many times I visited and tasted good Chinese food.
Must try chicken sizzler its very good quantity and quality. They serve rice, noodles and fries and chicken chilly.
Its very hot and delicious üòã
Best starter- veg crispy. I never tried like this its very crispy and saucy.
Also other Chinese dishes also very tasty.
Good portion and quality.
Ample of seating.","Images":null,"When":"a year ago"},{"Name":"Sunita Arya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJpihhNqlphJlWxHSt5PhNV0yFGWGIul02T8qnaLvhw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If you want to take a revenge on someone then order food from here.","Images":null,"When":"3 days ago"},{"Name":"Krrish Gupta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKXRDgNNqo6vWNT4kwR8C6kB8Aj1rcEmFayKjzuPcQ5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very worst Serving Quality And Food was too late coming  don't come To this restaurant ü§Æ","Images":null,"When":"a year ago"}]

[{"Name":"Nachiket Virkud","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4C51Cyrj94NeH7UJ8Xlg1UEa0k5K2_K0cUFRWjAJjf29w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Restaurant jas good accessibility from all sides. And also it has decent ambience.
The service is not that great but the atmosphere is very good and quiet.
The dishes we ordered where quiet decent and not so tasty they were having quiet the taste not as far as the hype the Recency Restaurant name has.
The chicken crispy we ordered was tasty, but as for the veg spring roll they were not so tasty and were very oily, i would recommend not ordering it at all.
The chicken lollipop we ordered weren't fresh or tender and the coating of the lollipop was really thin and the lollipop didn't had any taste of marination in it.","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNw8QEFAXHiRmr4pqLPMAWLDev0YPZhsjy17GvA=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNFJLxsv_bGsXqURz_Phryqbypfvut_FnAvzATl=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPolx2NqnAAXh7_F12mPxptV9dbQsMBeQnQwMo-=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN4Z2ZUhfrWJGuJr09j1k2IhSmjgwf30N_NObN0=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNiTZtqW4GvOnwVyupZhrAz_1pu5JrW2sagSYBL=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOshKB65wGb9eWWgJ9dbREejUtxmpt8_cKdbboe=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"5 months ago"},{"Name":"Tejas Watamwar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcwhIn2SVVP8MZ5yVF1Drj5v93EXfNVRJnaYlgNcRIJOs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of dining at Regency last week, and I must say, it was an outstanding experience from start to finish! The restaurant's ambience was truly delightful, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere that enhanced the entire dining experience.

Now, let's talk about the food ‚Äì it was absolutely fantastic! One dish, in particular, left me in awe: the Manchurian gravy. It was an explosion of flavors, perfectly balanced, and packed with deliciousness. The rich, tangy sauce coated the succulent Manchurian balls perfectly, making it an absolute treat for my taste buds. If you visit Regency, do not miss out on this mouthwatering delight!

Moreover, the staff at Regency were incredibly friendly and attentive throughout my visit. They greeted me with warm smiles, promptly seated me, and provided excellent recommendations from their extensive menu. Their genuine hospitality made me feel welcomed and added to the overall positive experience.

I would highly recommend Regency to anyone in search of a top-notch dining experience. Whether you're looking for a perfect evening out, a family gathering, or a special occasion, this restaurant ticks all the boxes. The ambience, the food, and the friendly staff make it a place worth visiting time and time again.

Thank you, Regency, for an unforgettable dining experience. Keep up the fantastic work!","Images":null,"When":"3 months ago"},{"Name":"Sukan ECE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYuUCjiSRcsYQUwsrgj6ac2ZB5J3nBOP8-IHueaRa-uA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Food is good , but the staffs are not friendly. [{"Name":"Vaibhav Ambashikar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYt6ANJqqqV2fxM9tqM1TAYGPu9rNJHiwAm2WEzkLR3J0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Al Fresco is a cozy spot near Dombivali East railway station. It's named after the open-air vibe it offers, with outdoor seating by the main road. Keep in mind, though, that it can get a bit noisy and warm due to the outdoor setup.

The food takes a bit longer to arrive, but the taste is totally worth it. The menu is packed with delicious options that make up for any wait.

Prices are a tad high, but you're paying for quality ingredients and the experience.

Don't forget to say hi to their friendly dog, Laura. She adds a nice touch to the place.

To sum it up, Al Fresco near Dombivali East station gives you an open-air dining experience, though it can be a bit noisy and warm. The food is yummy, the prices are a bit high, and Laura the dog is a bonus!","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPrps9ARvA4tWDWKqVyK_rYP2vlWvDcMXM4J_d2=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipO-9ZDY9Gf2fmJCc60AGfQFG1WFhJKSvrx1IYQh=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPLhzcyKBvScGDtkkEKLhuGbksyZWhMgMSI8A8E=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"a month ago"},{"Name":"Aditya Waghmare","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFe1LMBB4Ide_Zt_2uE3CkaLZGOav8YdbIRYXRKodahRgA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice cafe near Dombivli station to grab some food and coffee. It specializes in Pastas, Pizzas, variety of Appetizers. Food is good with ample quantity and appropriately priced. I went to the place for a dine-in. There was no continental sauce or no sauce in the sandwich. It was a dry sandwich.

There were slices of cucumber, tomato, capsicum just like we get at a thelewal or a streetside vendor.

Ideally a Paneer Tikka Panini Sandwich from a continental cafe should have good amount of lettuce, preferably shredded, rather all greens shredded, nicely quoted in a continental sauce. Paneer tikka doesn't mean you have to put a slab in the sandwich. You should dice or cube the panner and grill it properly with grilling masala or marination.

I used to order the same sandwich few months ago and it was never like this.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"vidisha pisal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQxbkj0O165Z1gmxHtiaGhrcA_bCbjk-1zf1u4CvfAG-37=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you are hardcore seafood or non veg lover then you guys cannot miss this place in Dombivil. This place serve one of the best konkan and malvani seafood. we are absolutely in love with the taste and quality of the food they serve over here. We ordered Surmai Thali in thali it includes Big piece of Surami, Rice, Bhakari, Jalwa,Solkadi,Almaner,Chutney and prawns curry . On the first bite itself our mind is blown up by the taste of masala on fish well marinated properly cooked amazing taste
then Tawa Pomplet Fry same properly cooked and very freshly made , Tawa Prawns fry which is made in garlic and perfect flavour of garlic and other masala comes together well blend taste
and apart from this you have to try there paya soup not so spicy but taste of spicy and everything when comes together the best dish comes on the table
I would Highly Recommeded this all dishes to go for it. And also they also organized events like Birthday party, Anniversary Party
Costing wise its 100% Worth it
Surmai Thali- Rs560
Prawns Tawa Fry - Rs 460

We ordered starters like chicken lollipop, chicken tandoori, surmai tava fry, prawns fry, paneer sizzler, cheese pakoda, etc. Everything was yum. [{"Name":"Kunal Bhatia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBeJoZ3sC1_L4V8sLuNPUmZGRhUKnuCAxSr895YoNLH9Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Have been ordering food from this restaurant for the past several years and never did the food disappoint me be it north Indian cuisine or Chinese, biryani etc,hence thought of writing a review...

They also have some excellent Shawarma's out of which what i found the best was Desi chef special shawarma and bbq shawarma fresh pita breads and loaded with veggies and mayonnaise and garlic mayonnaise tender chicken charred to perfection stuffed generously..!

I also tried their tandoori chicken kespa/kabsa rice again chicken was an absolute delight tender cooked perfectly well coated with masalas and beautifully presented even being a delivery and not a dine in impressive!!
Good indo-chinese dishes as well as north-indian cuisine..Hardly ever dissappointed with food quality or taste! Definitely a must try do give it a shot im sure it will be a good one.. Cheers.. As per my knowledge. This is their second branch at Manpada Road first branch is at Phadke Road Dombivli East. I ordered ragi Dosa and Rasam Vada ragi Dosa what is very basic and okay okay in test quality and presentation Sambar Chutney was as expected in any of the Udupi restaurants in Mumbai and suburbs. Not wow factor a Rasam Vada is the next dish which I ordered ball size Vadaj dipped in Rasam where very nice soft and spongy Rasam was too much sweet just like a sweet dish and with no flavours of Rasam. The only quality of Rasam was it was thin in consistency Overall it was okay okay experience","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOOizkAzeU7OipA7ukC0_RIG8NzCkdRjqtr8JQ=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPSKJloUJZrM1Jv3eFZxuAoyGAZR0QME6NlCGc=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMtEsPixBU5EdJYTKrlr1EeYHbBD164n_D3w4Y=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"3 weeks ago"},{"Name":"Shraddha Dev","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocISKRQikYBIK5480V_RHqhu-_YEDtF8l_Je1VP5xAsO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Whenever I come to dombivli my all time favourite restaurant is Modern Pride..

Rassam Vada one of my favourite & Mango ice-cream yummy.","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP4M6ub7jstFV-dwMK73tQwL3sVuAUN2vkUOF9-=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPKvgDzPQNZPGZNpFlt44bQn-LPo8Chonp0KNvs=w150-h150-k-no-p","https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPdyb6S-rbN_9d1XLkCOPVWwBRruA--nZzUyb6_=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"4 months ago"},{"Name":"sudarshan prabhudesai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVNe_Ri-ricB2rWar25pfO4b7NWDi8_UEs3cjYY2bAdw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":""I had the pleasure of dining at Hotel Modern Pride, and I must say that their food is truly delightful. The taste of every dish I tried was exceptional, and it's evident that they put a lot of effort into their culinary offerings. Whether you're a fan of local Indian cuisine  their menu has something to satisfy every palate. The dining experience was not only delicious but also accompanied by a pleasant ambiance, making it a memorable culinary journey."","Images":null,"When":"a month ago"},{"Name":"Niraj Joshi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcTRroojlyZP_As0q-Ndw2tQ0oFdqz2f610qLQW0Q6EA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Not recommend to visit this place. We visited yesterday and wasted money on 3 worst dishes I've ate in my entire life.

Food Review

1: Veg Lolipop - 1 out of 5 stars. Absolutely worst thing. Wasted 220 for this. They dipped bland paneer, mashroom and vegetable tikka into lollipop batter and fried it. Only good thing was the crispy batter. But not worth the price. Do not buy at any cost.

2: Cheese Pakoda - 0 out of 5 stars. How can you mess this up? Even a local restaurant make this better. Cheese was really sour and not even melted. It's like eating cold cheese in a fried batter. How's this even possible?

3: Neer Dosa - 4 out of 5 stars. This was a good thing dish and worth the money. Tasty. Recommended to order this.

4: Spring Roll - 3 out of 5 stars. It's fine. Taste is not as good as other fine dine restaurants but was served and cooed very well.

Service Review

Service is fast but waiters and captains are clueless and arrogant. They have waiters and captains running all over the place.

One dish is handled by 4 waiters before its served to customers.

When we were critical about the dish the captain had no clue and he simply ignored us. Seriously?

After all this they have the audacity to ask force tip.

Street food is far better than this horrible experience.","Images":["https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN5aOG190DmnU8sro3g4LJe9iTfgu2-mTDdbS67=w150-h150-k-no-p"],"When":"9 months ago"},{"Name":"Punit JVaidya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI5fqx1YpHyV4PvFB8veotHPc4qNyoBTscWNwSFmIOj=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is fantastic especially for pure veg lovers.
